@startuml
' @id(USE-VIEW-DIAGRAMS)
' @desc(USE-VIEW-DIAGRAMS, "Developer views a rendered model diagram on the in-app canvas with shapes and text legible.")
' @id(USE-FISHEYE-FOCUS)
' @desc(USE-FISHEYE-FOCUS, "Developer focuses on part of a diagram via a center-fixed fisheye that magnifies the canvas centre and compresses content toward the edges, layered on the scroll global zoom.")
' @id(USE-TOGGLE-PANELS)
' @desc(USE-TOGGLE-PANELS, "Developer collapses or expands the left MODELS panel and the right MODEL CONTEXT panel via an inner-edge handle, reclaiming canvas width on demand.")
' @id(USE-VIEW-OCL)
' @desc(USE-VIEW-OCL, "Implemented: selecting a .ocl file shows MddViewer::ocl_ui with a Source/Diagram toggle — Source paints the raw OCL text, Diagram paints the synthesized constraints SVG.")
' @id(USE-VIEW-DEPLOY)
' @desc(USE-VIEW-DEPLOY, "Implemented: MddViewer::new() loads a THIRD source, project.deploy_files(), beside model_registry() and cycle_registry(). The left rail renders a dedicated 'DEPLOY · /mdd-deploy · utility, not parity-gated' CollapsingHeader (shown in BOTH Directory and By-cycle modes) listing .mdd/deploy/**/*.puml; clicking a leaf reuses load_file to paint the existing .mdd/rendered/deploy/**/*.svg. lookup_file searches registry + deploy_files; deploy files never enter ModelRegistry, so Project::review()/validate() keep ignoring .mdd/deploy/.")
' @id(USE-VIEWER-THEMED)
' @desc(USE-VIEWER-THEMED, "Implemented as crates/mdd-viewer/src/theme.rs: run() calls theme::register_fonts(&cc.egui_ctx) once at startup (Inter Regular + Medium installed at the head of FontFamily::Proportional, JetBrains Mono Regular at the head of FontFamily::Monospace, egui defaults kept as fallback). MddViewer::update calls theme::apply_theme(ctx) FIRST each frame: dark_light::detect() → catppuccin_egui::set_theme(ctx, MOCHA | LATTE), then style.spacing.item_spacing = (8.0, 6.0) and rounding = 6.0 on every WidgetVisuals variant + window + menu. Pure chrome: theme.rs imports egui, catppuccin_egui, dark_light; it touches nothing under .mdd/ and doesn't enter ModelRegistry / CycleRegistry / DiagramPage paths.")
' @id(USE-VIEW-PUML-SOURCE)
' @desc(USE-VIEW-PUML-SOURCE, "Implemented: the CentralPanel toggle row now offers Diagram | Source | Diff (View enum gains View::Source). Clicking Source sets self.view = View::Source; update() dispatches to MddViewer::source_ui before the constraint/canvas branch. source_ui lazily reads the selected file's text into SourceView { loaded, source } (cached by path) and paints it in an egui::ScrollArea::both as read-only monospace labels — lines starting `' @` highlighted yellow (markers), `@start`/`@end` blue (directives), other `'` comments dimmed. No DiagramPage, usvg/resvg or render call: the source is read straight from disk, so it works even when the SVG is unrendered.")
' @id(USE-OPEN-RENDER)
' @desc(USE-OPEN-RENDER, "As built: the central-panel view-tab row has an 'Open render' button (MddViewer::update). It is enabled only when MddViewer::selected_render_slug() is Some — the selected file is a ModelKind::Mockup whose render mockups/src/mockups/<slug>.tsx exists under project.root(). Click runs open_mockup_render off the UI thread: probe :4317, spawn npm run dev in mockups/ if it is not already serving, then open the OS browser at /mockup/<slug>.")
' Current-side use-case view of the `mdd view` interactive diagram viewer,
' refreshed from code: the canvas applies a center-fixed fisheye over
' the base scroll zoom, the side panels collapse, the toolbar has no
' zoom buttons, .ocl files render via a Source/Diagram toggle, a
' dedicated non-gated DEPLOY section surfaces .mdd/deploy diagrams, the
' chrome is themed by a per-frame Catppuccin variant that follows the
' OS appearance with bundled Inter + JetBrains Mono fonts, and a
' central-panel Source toggle shows a model file's raw PlantUML text.
title mdd view — diagram viewer (current)

left to right direction

actor "Developer" as Dev

rectangle "mdd-viewer" {
  usecase "View rendered diagram\n(shapes AND text legible)" as View
  usecase "Browse model files" as Browse
  usecase "Pan and zoom canvas\n(scroll zoom, drag pan)" as PanZoom
  usecase "Focus via center fisheye" as Fisheye
  usecase "Collapse / expand side panels" as Panels
  usecase "Inspect model IDs and trace links" as Trace
  usecase "View OCL constraints\n(source or diagram)" as ViewOcl
  usecase "View deployment diagrams\n(dedicated DEPLOY section,\nNOT parity-gated)" as ViewDeploy
  usecase "View themed viewer chrome\n(Catppuccin, bundled fonts,\nOS appearance auto-follow)" as Themed
  usecase "View PlantUML source\n(Source toggle next to Diagram)" as ViewSource
  usecase "Open React mockup render\n(button opens browser)" as OpenRender
}

Dev --> View
Dev --> Browse
Dev --> PanZoom
Dev --> Fisheye
Dev --> Panels
Dev --> Trace
Dev --> ViewOcl
Dev --> ViewDeploy
Dev --> Themed
Dev --> ViewSource
Dev --> OpenRender

View ..> Browse : <<include>>
View ..> PanZoom : <<extend>>
View ..> Fisheye : <<extend>>
View ..> Panels : <<extend>>
View ..> Themed : <<include>>
View ..> ViewSource : <<extend>>
ViewOcl ..> PanZoom : <<extend>>
ViewDeploy ..> PanZoom : <<extend>>
OpenRender ..> Browse : <<include>>

note bottom of OpenRender
  Code (USE-OPEN-RENDER): the view-tab row adds an "Open render"
  button (MddViewer::update). Enabled only when
  MddViewer::selected_render_slug() is Some — the selection is a
  ModelKind::Mockup whose mockups/src/mockups/<slug>.tsx exists.
  Click runs open_mockup_render off-thread: mockup_server_up()
  probes :4317, spawns npm run dev in mockups/ if down, then
  open_in_browser opens /mockup/<slug>. Realized by
  SEQ-OPEN-RENDER; launcher CMP-MOCKUP-LAUNCH.
end note

note bottom of ViewOcl
  Code (USE-VIEW-OCL): when the selected file
  kind is Constraint, MddViewer::ocl_ui shows a
  Source | Diagram toggle. Source = raw .ocl
  text (read-only, @id/context/inv colored);
  Diagram = the synthesized constraints SVG
  (mdd_render::render_ocl_diagrams) painted via
  paint_canvas. Realized by SEQ-VIEW-OCL.
end note

note bottom of Fisheye
  Code (USE-FISHEYE-FOCUS): the canvas paints the
  rendered texture through a center-fixed fisheye mesh
  (CanvasView::fisheye_mesh / warp) — the centre bulges,
  content compresses toward the edges, corners stay put.
  Layered on the scroll-at-cursor base zoom; drag pans.
  Realized by SEQ-CANVAS-FISHEYE.
end note

note bottom of PanZoom
  The toolbar has no Reset / Zoom + / Zoom - buttons
  (removed). Zoom is scroll-only at the cursor; pan is
  drag-only. A small hint label replaces the buttons.
end note

note bottom of Panels
  Code (USE-TOGGLE-PANELS): each SidePanel renders an
  inner-edge chevron; clicking it sets PanelLayout
  collapsed and the panel shrinks to an exact-width
  sliver button that re-expands on click. Realized by
  SEQ-PANEL-COLLAPSE.
end note

note bottom of View
  Reads pre-rendered SVGs from .mdd/rendered/. If no
  models are mapped/rendered the canvas shows "No
  rendered output". Text rendering is realized by
  SEQ-RENDER-DIAGRAM-PAGE, which consults a populated
  font database (DOM-FONT-DATABASE) before rasterizing.
end note

note bottom of Themed
  Code (USE-VIEWER-THEMED): crates/mdd-viewer/src/theme.rs
  bundles assets/fonts/Inter-Regular.ttf, Inter-Medium.ttf,
  and JetBrainsMono-Regular.ttf via include_bytes!. run()
  registers them once through eframe's CreationContext.
  MddViewer::update's FIRST call is theme::apply_theme(ctx),
  which queries dark_light::detect(), picks
  catppuccin_egui::MOCHA / LATTE, and then mutates
  style.spacing.item_spacing and widget rounding. Realized
  by SEQ-APPLY-THEME, owned by CMP-VIEWER-THEME.
end note

note bottom of ViewDeploy
  Code (USE-VIEW-DEPLOY): MddViewer::new() calls
  project.deploy_files() as a third source; update()
  builds deploy_tree and renders a "DEPLOY" header
  ("/mdd-deploy · utility, not parity-gated") after
  the rail-mode match, so it shows in Directory AND
  By-cycle. Clicking a leaf -> lookup_file -> load_file
  paints .mdd/rendered/deploy/<rel>.svg on the shared
  canvas (same placeholder as any unrendered model if
  the SVG is absent). deploy_files() reuses
  render_sources(RenderTree::Deploy) and is NEVER in
  ModelRegistry. Realized by SEQ-VIEW-DEPLOY.
end note

note bottom of ViewSource
  Code (USE-VIEW-PUML-SOURCE): the CentralPanel toggle
  row is Diagram | Source | Diff. Clicking "Source" sets
  self.view = View::Source; update() calls
  MddViewer::source_ui (returning before the OCL/canvas
  branch). source_ui reads the selected file's text once
  into SourceView { loaded, source } and paints it via
  egui::ScrollArea::both as read-only monospace — `' @`
  marker lines yellow, `@start`/`@end` directives blue,
  other `'` comments dimmed. No DiagramPage / usvg call,
  so it works with no rendered SVG
  (OCL-PUML-SOURCE-NO-RENDER). Realized by
  SEQ-VIEW-PUML-SOURCE; state in DOM-PUML-SOURCE-VIEW.
end note
@enduml
